review:
A delightful terrifying story of love, jealousy, betrayal and mystery. The protagonist is invited to an island where the Kangale manor resides. He is the rightful heir of the property. Thus, on his arrival on the island he is greeted by the butler. Little does the protagonist know is the Kangale family history is filled with love triangles and murders. Soon as the poltergeist appears, our protagonist is set to unravel the mystery of the dead lovers and to free the manor of the haunting ghost. But would the superstitious butler let him? Would the ghost caught him? Would the protagonist die in the lighthouse fire as did the ghost? Help him out to find out!

PROS:
- Intriguing story;
- Beautiful scenery just like its predecessor;
- Music and environmental sounds;
- Few jumpscares;
- Hidden Objects;
- Main game + Bonus chapter.

CONS:
- No trading cards;
- No achievements.

It is a wonderful sequel. A new mystery, a new protagonist, a new story. Highly recommend it! I just love the graphics in these games. I little less light would have helped too. Yeah, I'm fan of the old games.
